25 mins Break
Continuous Version control 
GIT and its workflow
================================================

Demo 1 : Create a working directory, Create a local repo, and add the git configurations

# sudo su -

# mkdir myproject

# cd myproject 

# touch index1.html index2.html 

# git init 

# git config --global user.name admin

# git config --global user.email admin@gmail.com

Demo2: Add the files to git local repo

# git status

# git add .

# git status 

# git commit -m "added new files"

# git ls-files 

# git log

Demo 3: Modify the file and add the modifications to local repo -> restore

# echo "added content to file" >> index1.html

# echo "added content again to file" >> index1.html

# git status 

# git commit -a -m "done modifications"

# echo "added content again-2 to file" >> index1.html

# echo "added content again-3 to file" >> index1.html

Check the difference between 2 version of the same file 

# git diff index1.html

Discard changes in workign directory 

# git restore index1.html 

# cat index1.html

# echo "added content again-4 to file" >> index1.html

# git add .

take changes back to working directory - un-stage the staged changes 

# git restore --staged index1.html

# git commit -a -m "added modifications"
 
Demo 4:
Delete an existing file and delete it form working directory and local repo.

# git rm index1.html 

# git status 

# git commit -m "deleted file"

Demo 5: revert the changes back to its previous version

# git log --oneline 

copy the commit id (7 characters) of deleted file 

# git revert <commit id>

in the editor provide your comments
save the ditory - CTL X -> y -> enter key 

# git log --oneline 

# ls 

# git ls-files

Demo 6: Reset the commit history 

# git log --oneline 

copy the last commit id and not the recent commit id 

# git reset --hard <commit id>

# git log --oneline 

# ls

Demo 7: GIT Branching

Check the number of branchs 

# git branch 

create a new branch 

# git branch dev 

# git branch 

To work on branch - Switch to the branch 

# git checkout dev 

# git log --oneline 

Create a new commit on branch 

# touch dev_file1 

# git add .

# git commit -m "done on dev branch"

# git log --oneline 

Merge the chnages with master 

First switch to master 

# git checkout master

# git merge dev master 

# git log --oneline 

Delete the dev branch 

# git branch -d dev 








































































